article.description: Moseley, No. 14 Maryland cruise by Coppin State 110-51
article.headline: Moseley, No. 14 Maryland cruise by Coppin State 110-51
article.linkText: Moseley, No. 14 Maryland cruise by Coppin State 110-51
article.story:
BALTIMORE --  Brene Moseley had 18 points and eight assists and No. 14 Maryland cruised to a 110-51 victory over Coppin State on Sunday.

Shatori Walker-Kimbrough added 17 points on 6-of-7 shooting for the Terrapins (9-2), who broke the 100-point threshold on A'Lexus Harrison's putback with 4:27 left.

Harrison finished with a career-high 12 points and eight rebounds. Kiara Leslie added 13 points, Brionna Jones scored 12 and Laurin Mincy 10.

Maryland opened on a 7-0 run and led the entire way with a 59-25 advantage at the break. The Terrapins shot 58 percent from the floor, outrebounded the Eagles 44-28 and forced 29 turnovers.

Amber Griffin had 10 points and Bria Harris grabbed 11 rebounds to lead Coppin State (1-9).
